.TH KISH 1 "April 2026" "kish 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
kish \- the KI shell
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B kish
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] [\fISCRIPT\fR [\fIARGS\fR...]]
.SH DESCRIPTION
kish is a bash-compatible shell with native AI integration. It combines a full
POSIX shell (based on mvdan/sh) with an AI engine (OpenAI) that can be invoked
via the @ki prefix.
.PP
Without @ki, kish behaves exactly like bash. With @ki, it sends queries to the
configured AI provider and can execute commands autonomously (read-only) or with
user confirmation (write operations).
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-c \fIcommand\fR
Execute \fIcommand\fR and exit. Supports @ki prefix for AI queries.
.TP
.B \-i
Force interactive mode even when stdin is not a terminal.
.TP
.B \-l
Act as a login shell. Reads /etc/profile and ~/.profile.
.TP
.B \-v \fIlevel\fR
Verbose output for AI operations. 0=quiet (default), 1=show actions, 2=full debug.
.TP
.B \-\-norc
Do not read ~/.kishrc, ~/.bashrc, or /etc/bash.bashrc.
.TP
.B \-\-noprofile
Do not read /etc/profile, ~/.bash_profile, or ~/.profile.
.TP
.B \-\-version
Print version and exit.
.TP
.B \-\-help
Show help and exit.
.TP
.B \-\-web \fIaddr\fR
Start web UI on the given address (e.g. :12080). Provides a browser-based terminal
with KI panel, REST API, and token authentication. TLS is enabled by default.
.TP
.B \-\-token \fIstr\fR
Set authentication token for the web UI. If omitted, a random token is generated and printed.
.TP
.B \-\-insecure
Disable TLS for the web UI. Only use for local testing.
.SH KI COMMANDS
These commands are available in interactive mode:
.TP
.B @ki \fIquery\fR
Send a query to the AI engine. The prefix is configurable via ki.prefix in config.yaml.
.TP
.B ? [\fIquery\fR]
Quick context query. Without arguments, analyzes the last command and its output.
.TP
.B ki:status
Show AI engine status, memory count, and permissions.
.TP
.B ki:log [\fIn\fR]
Show last \fIn\fR shell log entries (default 20).
.TP
.B ki:search \fIquery\fR
Search the shell log for matching entries.
.TP
.B ki:audit [\fIn\fR]
Show last \fIn\fR audit log entries (default 20).
.TP
.B ki:clear
Reset conversation history.
.TP
.B ki:skills
List available skills (predefined scripts in ~/.kish/skills/).
.TP
.B ki:disk
Show disk usage of ~/.kish/ directory.
.TP
.B ki:costs
Show API cost tracking (today, total, recent requests).
.TP
.B showmemory [\fIfilter\fR]
Show persistent memory vault. Filter: \fBfacts\fR, \fBsessions\fR, \fBscratch\fR. Without filter: all categories.
.TP
.B showlogs [\fIfilter\fR] [\fIn\fR]
Show logs. Without filter: all categories. Filter: \fBshell\fR (commands + output), \fBaudit\fR (AI actions), \fBconversation\fR (AI dialog). \fIn\fR limits entries per category (default 20).
.TP
.B remember \fIkey\fR \fIvalue\fR
Store a fact in persistent memory. Also: \fBmerke\fR.
.TP
.B recall \fIquery\fR
Search persistent memory. Also: \fBerinnere\fR.
.TP
.B forget \fIkey\fR
Delete a fact from memory. Also: \fBvergiss\fR.
.SH SECURITY
kish uses a layered permission system for AI operations:
.PP
.B Action Levels:
.RS
.TP
.B AutoRead
Commands like ls, cat, grep, docker ps execute automatically.
.TP
.B Confirm
Write operations (rm, mv, git push) require user confirmation [j/n/e].
.TP
.B Blocked
AI cannot modify its own configuration (only hardcoded block).
.RE
.PP
All AI actions are logged to ~/.kish/audit.log. Secrets in shell output are
scrubbed before logging (API keys, passwords, JWTs, SSH keys).
.PP
Rate limiting: 20 queries/minute, 200 queries/hour (configurable).
.PP
The AI is only active when explicitly invoked via @ki. Shell commands without
@ki bypass the AI entirely.
.SH FILES
.TP
.B ~/.kish/config.yaml
AI provider configuration (provider, model, API key, prefix).
.TP
.B ~/.kish/permissions.yaml
Security settings (action levels, blocked commands, context filtering).
.TP
.B ~/.kish/kishrc
Shell startup file (aliases, functions, variables). Read on interactive startup.
.TP
.B ~/.kish/profile
Login profile. Read on login shell startup (after /etc/profile).
.TP
.B ~/.kish/history
Command history (readline, 10000 entries).
.TP
.B ~/.kish/shell.log
Persistent activity log with command output. Secret-scrubbed. Rotation at 5MB.
.TP
.B ~/.kish/audit.log
AI action audit trail. Append-only. Rotation at 10MB.
.TP
.B ~/.kish/vault/
Persistent AI memory. Subdirectories: fact/, session/, scratch/.
.TP
.B ~/.kish/completions/*.yaml
YAML-based tab completion specs for individual commands.
.TP
.B .kishrc
Project-local startup file. Read when entering a directory with this file.
.SH STARTUP FILES
.B Login shell:
/etc/profile \(-> ~/.bash_profile | ~/.bash_login | ~/.profile \(-> ~/.kish/profile
.PP
.B Interactive shell:
/etc/kish.kishrc | /etc/bash.bashrc \(-> ~/.kishrc | ~/.bashrc \(-> ./.kishrc
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B OPENAI_API_KEY
API key for OpenAI provider.
.TP
.B ANTHROPIC_API_KEY
API key for Anthropic provider (planned).
.TP
.B KISH_PS1
Custom prompt string (PS1-compatible escapes).
.TP
.B KISH_GOD_MODE=yes
Disable all hardcoded safety checks. Use at your own risk.
.SH COMPLETION SPECS
Tab completions for specific commands are defined in YAML files:
.PP
.nf
# ~/.kish/completions/git.yaml
subcommands:
  - checkout
  - commit
  - push
args:
  checkout: "$(git branch --format='%(refname:short)')"
  add: "$(git status --porcelain | cut -c4-)"
.fi
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
# Interactive shell
kish

# Run a command
kish -c 'echo hello'

# Ask AI
kish -c '@ki what does this error mean'

# Run script with arguments
kish script.sh arg1 arg2

# Debug AI operations
kish -v 2

# Pipe to AI
echo "error log" | kish -c 'ki "summarize"'
.fi
